04/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbian Justice Minister Vladan Batic, who also heads the state constitution commission, said Wednesday (3 September) that the final text of the Serbian Constitution would be completed by month's end.Once ready, the text will be discussed in public and voted on by parliament; only then would a 15 February referendum be held, Batic said. Earlier this week, acting Serbian President Natasa Micic said the date of the presidential election would be determined by progress in adopting the constitution.
In other news Wednesday, Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic said dialogue between Kosovo and Belgrade authorities should start immediately "to create conditions for the implementation of UN Security Council Resolution 1244". The Serbia-Montenegro Parliament meets Thursday to discuss the Kosovo issue. (Beta, B92 - 03/09/03)
